Name:         Blue Whale
Scientific:   Balaenoptera musculus
Class:        Mammalia
Habitat:      Ocean
Diet:         Carnivore (krill)
Lifespan:     80 years
Weight:       150000 kg
Status:       Endangered
Fact:         Largest animal ever known; heart is size of a small car

Name:         Tardigrade
Scientific:   Ramazzottius varieornatus
Class:        Tardigrada
Habitat:      Everywhere
Diet:         Omnivore
Lifespan:     2.5 years
Weight:       1e-07 kg
Status:       Least Concern
Fact:         Nearly indestructible; survives space vacuum, radiation, extreme temps

============================================================
  SCIENCE FACTS
============================================================

Domain:  Chemistry
Topic:   Avogadro's Number
Formula: N_A = 6.022×10²³ mol⁻¹
Note:    Number of atoms/molecules in one mole

Domain:  Chemistry
Topic:   Ideal Gas Law
Formula: PV = nRT
Note:    Pressure, volume, temperature relationship for ideal gas

Domain:  Mathematics
Topic:   Central Limit Theorem
Formula: Sample means → normal distribution
Note:    Foundation of statistical inference and polling

Domain:  Biology
Topic:   DNA Structure
Formula: Double helix; A-T and G-C base pairs
Note:    Stores and transmits genetic information

Domain:  Astronomy
Topic:   Hubble's Law
Formula: v = H₀ × d
Note:    Universe is expanding; galaxies recede from us

